<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,834,1183]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis box="[199,342,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[360,494,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–15" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1436,1458]" captionTargetBox="[292,1312,231,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-211@18.[262,1325,195,1420]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13–15. Beardius abbadi sp. n., male. 13—wing; 14—anal point and tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 15—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270898/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 14–15</figureCitation>
). Anal point bluntly triangular, 4–8, 6 µm long, not reaching posterior margin of tergite IX. Tergite IX without setae, tergal bands absent. Laterosternite IX with 2 setae. Phallapodeme 40–48, 46 µm long. Transverse sternapodeme 28–33, 30 µm long. Gonocoxite 91–114, 104 µm long. Superior volsella digitiform, 30–43, 38 µm long, with 7–8, 7 dorsal and 4 ventral setae, with microtrichia on ventral surface. Median volsella 2–4, 3 µm long, with 2–3, 3 apical setae, longest 18–25, 23 µm long. Inferior volsella clavate, 40–51, 46 µm long, with 2 apical setae and 4–5, 4 stout and 2 thin setae subapically; projection narrowly triangular, arising from base of volsella, 8–15, 11 µm long, covered with microtrichia. Gonostylus 111–127, 119 µm long. HR 0.72– 1.00, 0.88. HV 1.74–2.18, 2.00.
</paragraph>
